addPayOrder(address,address,uint256,uint.details: add a pay order, if your deposition is insufficient, your order will be disable.

params.buyAmount: the options token amount you want to buy.
params.deposit: you need to deposit some settlement currency to pay the order.deposit is the amount of settlement currency to pay.

addSellOrder(address,address,uint256).details: add a sell order. The Amount of options token will be transfered into contract address.

params.amount: the options token amount you want to sell.

addWhiteList(address).details: Implementation of add an eligible address into the whitelist.

buyOptionsToken(address,uint256,address,.details: buy amount options token form sell order.

params.amount: options token amount you want to buy
params.currencyAmount: the settlement currency amount will be payed for

getPayOrderList(address,address).details: getting all of the pay orders;
getPayOrderList(address,address).return: owner account, created time, buy amount, settlements deposition.

getSellOrderList(address,address).details: getting all of the sell orders;
getSellOrderList(address,address).return: owner account, created time, sell amount.

getTransactionFee().details: Returns the rate of trasaction fee.

getWhiteList().details: Implementation of getting the eligible whitelist.

isEligibleAddress(address).details: Implementation of testing whether the input address is eligible.

isOwner().details: Returns true if the caller is the current owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

redeemInvalidPayOrder(address,address).details: redeem a pay order.redeem the earliest pay order.return back the deposition.

redeemPayOrder(address,address).details: redeem a pay order.redeem the earliest pay order.return back the deposition.

redeemSellOrder(address,address).details: redeem a sell order.redeem the earliest sell order.return back the options token.

removeWhiteList(address).details: Implementation of revoke an invalid address from the whitelist.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

returnExpiredOrders().details: return back the expired options token orders. Both buy orders and sell orders

sellOptionsToken(address,uint256,address.details: sell amount options token to buy order.

params.amount: options token amount you want to sell

setTransactionFee(uint256,int32).details: set the rate of trasaction fee.

params.exponent: the exponent figures of transaction fee. transaction fee = Number(value,exponent);
params.value: the significant figures of transaction fee .

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
